	<Aux:TextAnnotations rdf:nodeID="bnode0B63FF2F-422F-48EB-8077-7AA10D4C1CE0">
		<Aux:document_text xml:lang="en-US">For the purposes of creating special provisions for potential losses under the portfolios of homogeneous credits the banks shall be entitled to form the portfolios from the credits granted to the natural persons. The credits the total amount of which under all agreements does not exceed 40 million Belarusian rubles in the aggregate for one borrower as at the date of risk assessment, may be included in the portfolios of homogeneous credits. The bank’s approaches to the creation of the portfolios of homogeneous credits, including the indicators of homogeneity, procedure, methods, and terms for including the credits in the portfolios of homogeneous credits, methodology, procedures for classifying and creating provisions for potential losses under the portfolios of homogeneous credits, as well as monitoring thereof, shall be specified in the bank’s local regulatory legal acts.</Aux:document_text>
